Rich folk and companies stepped forward offering insane money to buy Sticky Fingers and the precious recipe. Instead, Merdiy made one last batch for San Fransisco. On one side of the brown paper packaging she wrote "Give It Up And You Get It All", and on the other side? 4/5

The brownies were coveted, the recipe top secret. Each would be delivered wrapped in brown paper, which Meridy would doodle illustrations and inspirational messages on. When she decided to give up the business in the late eighties, she was selling upwards of 10,000 a month. 3/5

What started as recreational fun became medical relief during the AIDS crisis, with Meridy delivering brownies (and love) to isolated patients throughout the city at great personal risk, in an effort to help with their depression, insomnia, pain & loss of appetite. 2/5
